01/05/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Economy and Regional Development Minister Mladjan Dinkic was found guilty on Thursday (April 30th) of slander. 
He was ordered to pay the chairwoman of the national council for anticorruption efforts, Verica Barac, around 4,700 euros. 
Dinkic accused her, during a television programme appearance, of submitting falsified signatures when running for a post in the G17 Plus party, which Dinkic heads. 
(Beta, Tanjug, B92, RTS - 30/04/09)
